title: High Primary Education Completion Rate
description: In 2021, Spain achieved a remarkable persistence rate of 99.97% for students reaching grade 5 and 99.94% for those completing the last grade of primary education, showcasing its strong educational system.

title: Minimal Health Expenditure-Induced Poverty
description: As of 2019, only 0.01% of Spain's population was pushed further below the $3.65 poverty line due to out-of-pocket healthcare expenses, indicating effective healthcare policies.
